web_snippets: Maggie Nelson was born in 1973 and grew up in the San Francisco Bay Area. She received a BA from Wesleyan University in 1994 and a PhD from the Graduate Center.
Maggie Nelson is the author of several acclaimed books of poetry and prose, many of which have become cult classics defying categorization.
Maggie Nelson is a writer forging a new mode of nonfiction that transcends the divide between the personal and the intellectual.
